00:02:36,479 --> 00:03:05,740
A big piece of this is improving the walkability and the livability of our squares. Right now, you look at Medford Square, three of the five or six ways to get in here, nobody wants to walk to the square, because they're afraid they're going to get injured, hit by a car, stuck at a light. We really need to take a look at making our public squares more walkable, because that's how we get people there, that's how we get commercial development there, and that's how we make them places that people want to go. At the end of the day, we have something the developers want, and we have the power to make them play by our rules.

